<task id="001" project="ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2">
  <metadata>
    <title>B1 — Create 6 sprk_analysisaction rows in Spaarke Dev for Insights node ActionTypes</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <wave>B</wave>
    <estimated-effort>2h</estimated-effort>
    <tags>dataverse, mcp, sprk_analysisaction, jps-prompt-authoring, unblock-synthesis</tags>
    <dependencies>—</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <wave-item>B1</wave-item>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create 6 sprk_analysisaction rows in Spaarke Dev representing the Insights node ActionTypes (LiveFact, IndexRetrieve, EvidenceSufficiency, GroundingVerify, DeclineToFind, ReturnInsightArtifact). Each row carries its JPS-formatted system prompt in sprk_systemprompt (where applicable — e.g., DeclineToFind has a structured instruction; LiveFact may use a parametric template). This task is the load-bearing unblock that lets the existing predict-matter-cost@v1 playbook's nodes dispatch correctly. Without these rows, the JPS engine logs "Node X in batch 1 failed - stopping playbook execution" and the orchestrator returns the defensive scaffold decline.
  </prompt>

  <role>Dataverse engineer familiar with sprk_analysisaction schema + JPS prompt format + MCP tool usage.</role>

  <goal>
    6 new sprk_analysisaction rows live in Spaarke Dev, each with: action code (e.g., INSIGHTS.LIVE_FACT, INSIGHTS.INDEX_RETRIEVE, INSIGHTS.EVIDENCE_SUFFICIENCY, INSIGHTS.GROUNDING_VERIFY, INSIGHTS.DECLINE_TO_FIND, INSIGHTS.RETURN_INSIGHT_ARTIFACT), Action Type (FK to type taxonomy — to be confirmed against existing values), sprk_systemprompt (JPS-formatted JSON where applicable), description, tags, active=true. Rows discoverable by Deploy-Playbook.ps1 action-code lookup (task 003 adds the lint check).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/spec.md (§Wave B; §Terminology)</file>
    <file purpose="claude">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="r1-prompts">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/Prompts/*.txt</file>
    <file purpose="r1-playbook-json">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/Playbooks/predict-matter-cost.playbook.json</file>
    <file purpose="r1-node-executors">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Insights/Graph/</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec.md PR-1">All prompt content goes into sprk_analysisaction.sprk_systemprompt (the existing JPS primitive). NO new sprk_prompt entity.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md NFR-03">Every Insights playbook node must reference a sprk_analysisaction row.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-027">Schema additions flow through managed-solution promotion path. Since this is data (rows), not schema, single-env (Spaarke Dev) is acceptable for B1; Wave C/D may promote via solution.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>sprk_analysisaction, JPS prompt format, MCP Dataverse tools</topic>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/spec.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/dataverse-mcp-usage/SKILL.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Discover existing action-type taxonomy">Via mcp__dataverse__describe_table on sprk_analysisaction; identify the Action Type field options (e.g., 02 - Classification). For Insights node types not yet in the taxonomy, decide: add new option-set values now, or reuse generic "Custom" type. Document the choice.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Look up the existing "Classify Document" row as JPS prompt template">Use mcp__dataverse__read_query to fetch its sprk_systemprompt JSON. Use as the canonical structure ($schema, $version, instruction { role, task, constraints, context }, input, parameters).</step>
    <step order="3" name="Author 6 sprk_systemprompt JSON values">For LIVE_FACT: parametric instruction over current matter state. For INDEX_RETRIEVE: instruction for cohort + Precedent retrieval. For EVIDENCE_SUFFICIENCY: instruction for sufficiency rule evaluation. For GROUNDING_VERIFY: mechanical citation-check instruction. For DECLINE_TO_FIND: structured decline template. For RETURN_INSIGHT_ARTIFACT: artifact-shape instruction. Inputs/parameters per node-executor contract.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Create 6 rows via mcp__dataverse__create_record">action codes INSIGHTS.LIVE_FACT, INSIGHTS.INDEX_RETRIEVE, INSIGHTS.EVIDENCE_SUFFICIENCY, INSIGHTS.GROUNDING_VERIFY, INSIGHTS.DECLINE_TO_FIND, INSIGHTS.RETURN_INSIGHT_ARTIFACT. Each: name, sprk_systemprompt (JSON), description, tags, active=true.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Verify rows queryable">mcp__dataverse__read_query — confirm all 6 returned with expected sprk_systemprompt content.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Document action codes">Update spec.md Affected Areas (or a notes/ scratch file) with the 6 final action codes for downstream tasks (002, 003, 004).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__describe_table">Discover taxonomy</tool>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__read_query">Look up template + verify</tool>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__create_record">Author the 6 rows</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="dataverse-data">6 sprk_analysisaction rows in Spaarke Dev</output>
    <output type="notes">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/notes/drafts/wave-b-action-codes.md (final action codes + JPS prompt content per row)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">6 sprk_analysisaction rows queryable in Spaarke Dev with the documented action codes</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Each row's sprk_systemprompt is valid JSON conforming to the JPS schema (verified against the "Classify Document" pattern)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Each row's sprk_isactive = true</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Action codes documented in notes/drafts/wave-b-action-codes.md for downstream tasks</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
